  <brief_title>Phase2, Single Group, Open Clinical Trial to Evaluate the Efficacy and Safety of Roflumilast in Symptomatic Bronchiectasis Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Seoul National University Bundang Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Seoul National University Bundang Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There is currently no effective treatment of bronchiectasis other than treating its
      complications such as infection, bleeding, etc. Roflumilast is a newly developed
      anti-inflammatory drug that has proven to be effective in stable COPD. We hypothesized that
      Roflumilast might be effective in symptomatic bronchiectasis patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
